'''东亚'''泛指[[亚洲|亚洲]]東部，具有[[地理|地理]]<ref name=encarta-east-asia>{{cite web |url = http://encarta.msn.com/dictionary_1861672714/East_Asia.html |title = East Asia |accessdate = 2008-01-12 |work = [[Encarta|Encarta]] |publisher = Microsoft |quote = the countries and regions of Mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, Mongolia, South Korea, North Korea and Japan. |archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5kwbU9Hqq?url=http://encarta.msn.com/dictionary_1861672714/East_Asia.html |archivedate = 2009-10-31 |deadurl = yes |df =  }}</ref>和[[文化|文化]]<ref name=easia-columbia>[http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/webcourse/key_points/kp_5.htm Columbia University – "East Asian cultural sphere"] {{Wayback|url=http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/webcourse/key_points/kp_5.htm |date=20080227154316 }} "The East Asian cultural sphere evolves when Japan, Korea, and what is today Vietnam all share adapted elements of Chinese civilization of this period (that of the Tang dynasty), in particular Buddhism, Confucian social and political values, and literary Chinese and its writing system."</ref>层面上的双重意义<ref name="Prescott 2015">{{Cite book |title = East Asia in the World: An Introduction |last=Prescott |first= Anne |publisher=Routledge |year=2015 |isbn=978-0765643223}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |title=Modern East Asia: An Introductory History |last=Miller |first=David Y. |publisher=Routledge |year=2007 |isbn=978-0765618221 |pages=xxi–xxiv}}</ref>。东亚地区通常包括[[中国大陆|中国大陆]]、[[日本列岛|日本列岛]]、[[台湾|台湾]]、[[朝鲜半岛|朝鲜半岛]]、[[海南岛|海南岛]]、[[琉球群島|琉球群島]]和[[蒙古高原|蒙古高原]]等地<ref name="encarta-east-asia"/><ref name="Prescott 2015"/><ref name="Kort 2005 7">{{cite book |title=The Handbook Of East Asia |last=Kort |first=Michael |publisher=Lerner Publishing Group |year=2005 |isbn=978-0761326724 |page=7 |url=https://archive.org/details/handbookofeastas0000kort }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www1.essex.ac.uk/armedcon/world/asia/east_asia/default.htm |title=Country Profiles: East Asia |website=Children and Armed Conflict Unit at the University of Essex |accessdate=2019-09-01 |archive-date=2020-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411182322/https://www1.essex.ac.uk/armedcon/world/asia/east_asia/default.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=East Asia |url=https://link.springer.com/journal/12140 |publisher=Springer Netherlands |journal= |access-date=2019-09-01 |archive-date=2019-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702141706/https://link.springer.com/journal/12140 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://asiasociety.org/china-korea-and-japan-forgiveness-and-mourning |title=China, Korea and Japan: Forgiveness and Mourning |last=Seybolt |first=Peter J. |website=Center for Asian Studies |publisher=Center for Asian Studies |accessdate=2019-09-01 |archive-date=2019-12-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211220823/https://asiasociety.org/china-korea-and-japan-forgiveness-and-mourning |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Asian History Module Learning">{{cite book |title=Asian History Module Learning |publisher=Rex Bookstore Inc. |year= 2002 |isbn=978-9712331244 |page=186}}</ref><ref name="Salkind 2008 56">{{cite book |title=Encyclopedia of Educational Psychology |url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaeduc00salk |last=Salkind |first=Neil J. |publisher=Sage Publications |year=2008 |isbn = 978-1412916882 |page=[https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaeduc00salk/page/n85 56]}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=A History of East Asia: From the Origins of Civilization to the Twenty-First Century |last=Holcombe |first= Charles |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2010 |isbn=978-0521731645 |page=3}}</ref>，面積约1170萬平方公里<ref>{{cite book|author1=王志艳|title=地理百科知识博览·我的第一本百科书|date=2013|publisher=天津人民出版社|isbn=7201079670|chapter=亚洲主要地理分区}}</ref><ref name = "台灣的選擇：地緣悲情之子，還是領先東亞轉大人_2017">{{cite web | title = 台灣的選擇：地緣悲情之子，還是領先東亞轉大人 | url = https://opinion.udn.com/opinion/story/6067/2736919 | publisher = 聯合報 | author = 范疇 | language = zh-tw | date = 2017-10-03 | accessdate = 2018-08-20 | archive-date = 2018-08-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180820203458/https://opinion.udn.com/opinion/story/6067/2736919 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。东亚地区居住有16亿人口，占世界人口的22%，亦是世界上人口稠密的地区之一，[[人口密度|人口密度]]達到133人每平方公里，约是世界平均水平的三倍。[[臺北市|台北]]、[[东京|东京]]、[[香港|香港]]、[[广州|广州]]、[[北京|北京]]、[[首尔|首尔]]、[[上海|上海]]、[[深圳|深圳]]等世界范围内人口稠密的城市皆位于东亚。

东亚地区是[[文明摇篮|文明摇篮]]，[[黄河|黄河]]和[[长江|长江]]流域较早产生人口稠密的农业社会，孕育出古老的[[中华文明|中华文明]]<ref>{{cite book |title = Towards a Sustainable Asia: The Cultural Perspectives |url = https://archive.org/details/towardssustainab00libg_856 |author = Association of Academies of Sciences in Asia |publisher=Springer |year=2012 |isbn= 978-3642166686 |page=[https://archive.org/details/towardssustainab00libg_856/page/n32 17]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |title = Ethnic Groups of North, East, and Central Asia: An Encyclopedia |last= Minahan |first= James B. |publisher=ABC-CLIO |year=2014 |isbn=978-1610690171 |pages = xx–xxvi}}</ref>。漢字文化為東亞文明共同瑰寶<ref>{{Cite book |title = Relational, Networked and Collaborative Approaches to Public Diplomacy: The Connective Mindshift |last= Zaharna |first= R.S. |last2=Arsenault |first2= Amelia |last3=Fisher |first3= Ali |publisher=Routledge |year=2013 |isbn=978-0415636070 |edition=1st |publication-date = 2013-05-01 |page=93}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title = A History of East Asia: From the Origins of Civilization to the Twenty-First Century |last= Holcombe |first=Charles |publisher=Cambridge University Press |year=2017 |isbn=978-1107544895 |page=13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |title=A Companion to Chinese History |last=Szonyi |first=Michael |publisher=Wiley-Blackwell |year=2017 |isbn=978-1118624609 |page=90}}</ref>，包括[[台灣文化|台灣]]、[[中國文化|中國]]、[[日本文化|日本]]、[[朝鲜文化|韓國]]和[[越南文化|越南]]文化，形成於东亚的[[汉字文化圈|东亚文化圈]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/main_pop/kpct/ct_china.htm|title=Central Themes for a Unit on China {{!}} Central Themes and Key Points {{!}} Asia for Educators {{!}} Columbia University|website=afe.easia.columbia.edu|access-date=2018-12-01|archive-date=2018-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181210042404/http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/main_pop/kpct/ct_china.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。源于[[文言|古典汉语]]的詞彙廣泛流傳於當代[[日语|日语]]、[[朝鲜语|朝鲜语]]、[[越南语|越南语]]；明治維新後的日本，在外來語翻譯中參考漢字古籍，成為[[和制漢語|和制漢語]]；大清帝國晚期至大清帝國結束後的[[新文化運動|新文化運動]]、[[白話文運動|白話文運動]]，在外來詞彙及白話文結構上大量參照日語翻譯、日語文法，[[台灣|台灣]]在[[日本歷史|日本時代]]受到日語文化影響，在今日[[台語|台語]]有許多源自[[日語|日語]]的詞彙，源自東亞大陸的[[夏历|夏历]]和[[汉字|汉字]]至今影響[[漢字文化圈|漢字文化圈]]<ref name="Goscha 2016">{{Cite book |title=The Penguin History of Modern Vietnam: A History |last= Goscha |first= Christopher |publisher= Allen Lane |year=2016 |isbn= 978-1846143106}}</ref><ref name="Kang 2012 33–34">{{cite book |title=East Asia Before the West: Five Centuries of Trade and Tribute |last=Kang |first=David C. |publisher=Columbia University Press |year=2012 |isbn=978-0231153195 |pages=33–34}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title=The Triple Package: How Three Unlikely Traits Explain the Rise and Fall of Cultural Groups in America | url=https://archive.org/details/triplepackagehow0000chua | publisher=Penguin Press HC |author1 = Amy Chua |author2 = Jed Rubenfeld | year=2014 |page=[https://archive.org/details/triplepackagehow0000chua/page/122 122] |isbn=978-1594205460}}</ref><ref name="Walker 2012 2">{{cite book |title=East Asia: A New History |last=Walker |first=Hugh Dyson |publisher=AuthorHouse |year=2012 |page=2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |title=China's Cosmopolitan Empire: The Tang Dynasty |last=Lewis |first=Mark Edward |publisher=Belknap Press |year=2012 |isbn= 978-0674064010 |publication-date=April 9, 2012 |page=156}}</ref><ref name="Reischauer">Edwin O. Reischauer, "The Sinic World in Perspective," ''Foreign Affairs ''52.2 (January 1974): 341—348. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/20038053 JSTOR] {{Wayback|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/20038053 |date=20170115220455 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |title=Asia Civilizations: Ancient to 1800 AD |last= Lim |first= SK |publisher=ASIAPAC |isbn=978-9812295941 |page=89|date= 2011-11-01 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Redesigning Asian Business: In the Aftermath of Crisis |url=https://archive.org/details/redesigningasian0000rich |last= Richter |first=Frank-Jurgen |publisher=Quorum Books |year=2002 |isbn=978-1567205251 |page=[https://archive.org/details/redesigningasian0000rich/page/15 15]}}</ref><ref name="Hazen 2005 1">{{cite book |title=Building Area Studies Collections |last= Hazen |first= Dan |last2=Spohrer |first2=James H. |publisher=Otto Harrassowitz |year=2005 |isbn=978-3447055123 |publication-date = 2005-12-31 |page=1}}</ref>，可知東亞文明的交流十分密切。全东亚流行的主要[[宗教|宗教]]为[[佛教|佛教]]，中国古典的[[儒家|儒家]]思想理念亦深刻影响东亚人的传统观念<ref name="Salkind 2008 56"/>。

东亚部分国家或地区在现代化转型中取得成功，随着亞洲經濟的崛起，该区域在世界上的政治、经济重要性正日益提升。[[日本|日本]]最早成功实行[[現代化|現代化]]、[[工業化|工業化]]，实现国力增长，为全球最富裕发达的国家之一；[[韩国|韩国]]、[[Taiwan|台湾]]和[[香港|香港]]在20世纪60至90年代实现经济腾飞，为[[亚洲四小龙|亚洲四小龙]]中的三者，被列为发达经济体。[[中华人民共和国经济|中华人民共和国经济]]自20世纪末起亦发展迅速，2010年中国超越日本成为世界第二大经济体，仅次于[[美国|美国]]，中华人民共和国如今已被视为[[潜在超级大国|潜在超级大国]]之一。虽然东亚在政治和经济上具有较大影响力，但现存的如朝鲜与韩国之间的[[朝鮮半島統一問題|朝鮮半島問題]]，[[中華人民共和國|中國]]与[[Taiwan|台灣]]之间的[[台海安全問題|台海安全問題]]，中華人民共和國、中華民國与日本领土争端的[[钓鱼岛问题|釣魚臺列嶼问题]]和日本、韩國之间的[[独岛问题|独岛问题]]是影响该地区未来发展的安全隐患。

